From: Jussi Kivilinna <jussi.kivilinna@mbnet.fi>
Date: Mon, 7 Jun 2010 00:56:27 -0700
Subject: asix: check packet size against mtu+ETH_HLEN instead of
 ETH_FRAME_LEN
Patch-mainline: v2.6.35
Git-commit: 9227a46bfbac0516fb7428715a095e1bc59b872a

Driver checks received packet is too large in asix_rx_fixup() and fails if it is. Problem is
that MTU might be set larger than 1500 and asix fails to work correctly with VLAN tagged
packets. The check should be 'dev->net->mtu + ETH_HLEN' instead.

Tested with AX88772.

Signed-off-by: Jussi Kivilinna <jussi.kivilinna@mbnet.fi>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@suse.de>

---
 drivers/net/usb/asix.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/usb/asix.c
+++ b/drivers/net/usb/asix.c
@@ -343,7 +343,7 @@ static int asix_rx_fixup(struct usbnet *
 			return 2;
 		}
 
-		if (size > ETH_FRAME_LEN) {
+		if (size > dev->net->mtu + ETH_HLEN) {
 			netdev_err(dev->net, "asix_rx_fixup() Bad RX Length %d\n",
 				   size);
 			return 0;
